"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:5.18.1.4\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">5.18.1.4</span> 标题：钱囊、钱箱、宝盒（money box, treasure box）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">经文出处</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希：γλωσσόκομον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：glōssokomon)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:6\">JHN 12:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:29\">JHN 13:29</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希：θησαυρός</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：thēsauros)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:11\">MAT 2:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:35\">MAT 12:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:35\">MAT 12:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:52\">MAT 13:52</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:45\">LUK 6:45</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希：κιβωτός</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：kibōtos)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Esd1:51\">1ES 1:51</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述和用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/OAI-0060_box_with_coins_and_jewels.png\" alt=\"OAI-0060_box_with_coins_and_jewels\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\"> (Image generated by ChatGPT using OpenAI technology)</figcaption></figure>钱箱是一种箱子，可能是木头做的，里面放着钱或其他贵重的小物品。这种箱子可能很小，可以轻松地单手拿着或夹在腋下。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻译</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>“宝盒”可以译为：“装着贵重物品的盒子”，或“装着值一大笔钱的物品的盒子。”</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:29\">JHN 13:29</a> 的重点并不是钱箱这件东西，而是犹大所承担的职责。因此，对于字面意为“犹大带着钱箱”的短句，可以简单地译为“犹大是管钱的”（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr> 直译），或“犹大是他们的财务”。这里的希腊文表达可以理解为惯用语。</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:11\">MAT 2:11</a> ：<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 把这里的希腊文<em>thēsaurus</em> 译为“treasures”（“宝物”），该词既可以指存放起来的贵重物品，也可能指储存贵重物品的地方或物件。对于该节经文中的这个词语，各译本分别译为“宝物”或“宝箱”；但即便是依循第二种解释，解经家对箱子的性质也没有达成共识。例如，有些人建议译为“宝盒”，而另一些人则不认同，主张译为“袋子”。鉴于<em>thēsaurus</em> 有许多译法，但又没有一种特别有说服力，因此最好按照目标语言中最自然且不与圣经文化冲突的方式来翻译。与圣经文化矛盾的翻译包括“手提箱”、“旅行箱”、“保险箱”等。翻译者要避免使用这些词语。许多翻译者都使用了“行李”和“用来装贵重物品的袋子（或箱子）”之类的一般性表达。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
